Description: Extra Portal whitelist servers or ip-addresses which are allowed to call REST services from the portal. REST services in the portal can either be called by authenticated users, or without authentication when the requester's IP address of hostname is in the whitelist.
This is especially useful for server configurations with multiple network cards where database servers calls seem to come from "another" ip-address. In this case these ip-addresses can be added here as a comma-separated list.
Most of the time this field can be left empty, because all machinenames in the Infrastucture tab and database servers in the configuration tab are automatically added to the Portal's whitelist by ipli.

Description: true / false value, whether or not Active Directory based LDAP authentication is enabled. If enabled, the urls of the AD servers must be specified, separated by a white space. Also the AD Domain must be specified.

Description:
Put value on true If using another device configured and terminating SSL before reaching OHS, then OHS must send https responses back to the client. OHS is not always responsible for sending https headers, but in the case it may, it needs specific directives in place. An example request flow as follows, noting where https stops:
Browser --> https --> LBR --> http --> OHS/mod_wl_ohs --> http --> WLS
